==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plotinist
<hw>Plo*ti"nist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A disciple of <persfn>Plotinus</persfn>, a celebrated
Platonic philosopher of the third century, who taught that the human
soul emanates from the divine Being, to whom it reunited at
death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

